# Scribe Cloud runs entirely on Cloudflare (Worker + static assets) — no server secrets needed.
#
# Public client config lives in public/config.json (committed; values are public / RLS-protected):
#   supabaseUrl, supabaseAnonKey (publishable key), asrUrl (HF Space)
#
# The Worker's Workers AI binding is declared in wrangler.jsonc ("ai": { "binding": "AI" }) and
# auto-provisions on `wrangler deploy` — there is NO API key to set.
#
# Burmese ASR = MMS (facebook/mms-1b-all) on the HF Space, int8 quantized.
# Tamil/Chinese = Dolphin/SeamlessM4T on the same Space.
# English/Japanese/Malay = Cloudflare Workers AI Whisper in worker.js.
#
# HF Space optional env vars (set in Space Settings → Variables and secrets):
#   GEMINI_API_KEY      — enables Gemini (gemini-flash) translation for unmatched Burmese
#   OPENAI_API_KEY      — enables OpenAI (gpt-4o-mini) fallback translation
#   SCRIBE_MY_SNAP=1    — tiered snapping (CER/TF-IDF/LaBSE), on by default
#   SCRIBE_MY_SEMANTIC=1 — LaBSE semantic tier, on by default (adds ~470MB cold-start)
#   SCRIBE_MY_QUANT=1   — int8 quantization for MMS, on by default
#   SCRIBE_MY_LM=0      — char n-gram LM decoding, off by default (slow on CPU)
